# The movement to the new exploration position has been executed successfully. 
# Now that I'm in this new area, I will search for any nearby resource patches, particularly focusing on iron ore or other useful materials.
#
# Let's check for resource patches within a radius of 50 tiles from my current position.

# Searching for nearby iron ore or other resource patches around the new position.
nearby_resource_patches = get_resource_patch(Resource.IronOre, position=new_explore_position, radius=50)

# Print the details of any iron ore patches or other resource types found in this area.
print(f'Nearby Resource Patches from the new position: {nearby_resource_patches}')  # Display found resource patches.
